{"title":"Molecular Nodes","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Molecular Nodes","format":"html"},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\nMolecular nodes is a project that I have been working on for the efficient import of structural biology data into the 3D modelling and animation program Blender. \n\nFor more details on the Molecular Nodes project, check out either the [github page](https://github.com/bradyajohnston/MolecularNodes) or the [documentation](https://bradyajohnston.github.io/MolecularNodes).\n\n\n<center>\n\n{{< youtube CvmFaRVmZRU >}}\n\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">DNA is now part of Molecular Nodes!<br><br>You can extract DNA from structures, procedurally create new DNA, use custom bases, join and break strands, colour it &amp; make it look pretty. All from within <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/blender3d?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#blender3d</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/geometrynodes?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#geometrynodes</a>!<br><br>Check it out: <a href=\"https://t.co/NEV3AxA8Yj\">https://t.co/NEV3AxA8Yj</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/Wcr9h3bJZP\">pic.twitter.com/Wcr9h3bJZP</a></p>&mdash; Brady Johnston (@bradyajohnston) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/bradyajohnston/status/1548970211318964224?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">July 18, 2022</a></blockquote> <script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script> \n\n</center>"},"formats":{"html":{"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-yaml":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig